Using a top-level looking like this

    module m #(parameter p = 0);
      initial $display(p);
    endmodule

I noticed that passing a parameter -Pm.p=true evaluates to 0.000. I guess the correct solution is to pass -Pm.p="true" instead, but I got a bit surprised when I noticed that every unqouted string containing the letter 'e' was parsed as a float. I would argue for either a stricter test for floats and/or treating it as a string if it fails to be parsed as a int or float

Also, probably a non-argument, but ModelSim, Isim and Xsim all treat the unquoted string as a string, that evaluates to 0x74727565
